                                     DDL & DML
                                   =============
DDL – Full Form
DDL = Data Definition Language

Work / Purpose
--------------
DDL is used to define, create, modify, and delete the structure of database objects.
It works on the schema (structure) of the database, not on the data itself.

What DDL Does?
--------------
Creates tables, databases, indexes, views
Changes table structure (add / modify columns)
Deletes database objects permanently

Key Points
-----------
Affects database structure
Changes are auto-committed (cannot be rolled back)
Used mainly by database designers / administrators

DDL Commands
------------
CREATE – creates database objects
ALTER – modifies existing objects
DROP – deletes objects permanently
TRUNCATE – removes all records but keeps structure
RENAME – renames database objects

DML–Full Form
DML = Data Manipulation Language

Work / Purpose
--------------
DML is used to insert, update, delete, and retrieve data from database tables.
It works on the data inside the table, not the structure.

What DML Does?
-------------
